=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_HPZ1_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 52 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with highpass character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: highpass
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 51.9132
  harmonic_decay_rate: 3.6448
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9181
  pitch_clarity: 2.0928
  inharmonicity: 0.0429
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: 17.8050
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: HPZ1 Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/HPZ1.html
// Tags: HPZ1, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// Compare:

{ WhiteNoise.ar(0.25) }.play;

{ HPZ1.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.25)) }.play;

// HPZ1 is useful to detect changes in a signal:
// see also HPZ2
(
{
    var changingSignal = LFNoise0.ar(1000);
    var hpz1 = HPZ1.ar(changingSignal);
    [hpz1, hpz1 > 0, hpz1.abs > 0]
}.plot
);
